detial.description:
Aviation and transport is a course that focuses on the study of transportation systems, with a particular emphasis on aviation. The course covers a wide range of topics related to aviation and transportation, including aircraft design, air traffic control, airport operations, logistics, and supply chain management.
            Students in this course typically study the principles of aerodynamics, aircraft systems, and aviation regulations. They may also learn about airport design, ground handling, and the management of air traffic control systems.
            In addition to aviation-specific topics, the course may also cover broader transportation-related topics such as transportation planning, transportation economics, and environmental impacts of transportation systems.
            Throughout the course, students may have the opportunity to participate in practical training such as flight simulations, field trips to airports, and internships with aviation and transportation companies.
            Upon completion of the course, graduates may find employment in a variety of roles within the aviation and transportation industries, including airline and airport management, logistics and supply chain management, air traffic control, and aircraft design and manufacturing.
            Overall, the aviation and transport course provides students with a strong foundation in the principles and practices of aviation and transportation, preparing them for successful careers in these dynamic and growing industries.
requirements: Professional Bachelor Degree in Aviation Transport and /or 5th Level Professional Qualification in Aviation Transport (2 years).
Bachelor Degree of Engineering Science in Mechanical Engineering (for studies majoring in Aviation Transport) or Electrical Engineering (for studies majoring in Avionics) (3 years).
